b'[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)  \n[English](../gita/bg05.htm)  \n[Previous](bgs04.htm)  [Next](bgs06.htm)\n\n* * *\n\nV. atha pa\xc3\xb1camodhy\xc4\x81ya\xe1\xb8\xa5. (sa\xe1\xb9\x83ny\xc4\x81sayoga\xe1\xb8\xa5)  \n  \narjuna uv\xc4\x81ca  \n  \nsa\xe1\xb9\x83ny\xc4\x81sa\xe1\xb9\x83 karma\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 k\xe1\xb9\x9b\xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\x87a punar yoga\xe1\xb9\x83 ca \xc5\x9ba\xe1\xb9\x83sasi  \nyac chreya etayor eka\xe1\xb9\x83 tan me br\xc5\xabhi suni\xc5\x9bcitam 5.1  \n  \n\xc5\x9br\xc4\xabbhagav\xc4\x81n uv\xc4\x81ca  \n  \nsa\xe1\xb9\x83ny\xc4\x81sa\xe1\xb8\xa5 karmayoga\xc5\x9b ca ni\xe1\xb8\xa5\xc5\x9breyasakar\xc4\x81v ubhau  \ntayos tu karmasa\xe1\xb9\x83ny\xc4\x81s\xc4\x81t karmayogo vi\xc5\x9bi\xe1\xb9\xa3yate 5.2  \n  \nj\xc3\xb1eya\xe1\xb8\xa5 sa nityasa\xe1\xb9\x83ny\xc4\x81s\xc4\xab yo na dve\xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\xadi na k\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x85k\xe1\xb9\xa3ati  \nnirdvandvo hi mah\xc4\x81b\xc4\x81ho sukha\xe1\xb9\x83 bandh\xc4\x81t pramucyate  \n5.3  \n  \ns\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83khyayogau p\xe1\xb9\x9bthag b\xc4\x81l\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5 pravadanti na pa\xe1\xb9\x87\xe1\xb8\x8dit\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nekam apy \xc4\x81sthita\xe1\xb8\xa5 samyag ubhayor vindate phalam  \n5.4  \n  \nyat s\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83khyai\xe1\xb8\xa5 pr\xc4\x81pyate sth\xc4\x81na\xe1\xb9\x83 tad yogair api  \ngamyate  \neka\xe1\xb9\x83 s\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83khya\xe1\xb9\x83 ca yoga\xe1\xb9\x83 ca ya\xe1\xb8\xa5 pa\xc5\x9byati sa pa\xc5\x9byati 5.5  \n  \nsa\xe1\xb9\x83ny\xc4\x81sas tu mah\xc4\x81b\xc4\x81ho du\xe1\xb8\xa5kham \xc4\x81ptum ayogata\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nyogayukto munir brahma nacire\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81dhigacchati 5.6  \n  \nyogayukto vi\xc5\x9buddh\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81 vijit\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81 jitendriya\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nsarvabh\xc5\xabt\xc4\x81tmabh\xc5\xabt\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81 kurvann api na lipyate 5.7  \n  \nnaiva ki\xe1\xb9\x83cit karom\xc4\xabti yukto manyeta tattvavit  \npa\xc5\x9bya\xc3\xb1 \xc5\x9b\xe1\xb9\x9b\xe1\xb9\x87van sp\xe1\xb9\x9b\xc5\x9ba\xc3\xb1 jighrann a\xc5\x9bnan gacchan svapa\xc3\xb1  \n\xc5\x9bvasan 5.8  \n  \npralapan vis\xe1\xb9\x9bjan g\xe1\xb9\x9bh\xe1\xb9\x87ann unmi\xe1\xb9\xa3an nimi\xe1\xb9\xa3ann api  \nindriy\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\xabndriy\xc4\x81rthe\xe1\xb9\xa3u vartanta iti dh\xc4\x81rayan 5.9  \n  \nbrahma\xe1\xb9\x87y \xc4\x81dh\xc4\x81ya karm\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87i sa\xe1\xb9\x85ga\xe1\xb9\x83 tyaktv\xc4\x81 karoti ya\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nlipyate na sa p\xc4\x81pena padmapatram iv\xc4\x81mbhas\xc4\x81 5.10  \n  \nk\xc4\x81yena manas\xc4\x81 buddhy\xc4\x81 kevalair indriyair api  \nyogina\xe1\xb8\xa5 karma kurvanti sa\xe1\xb9\x85ga\xe1\xb9\x83 tyaktv\xc4\x81tma\xc5\x9buddhaye  \n5.11  \n  \nyukta\xe1\xb8\xa5 karmaphala\xe1\xb9\x83 tyaktv\xc4\x81 \xc5\x9b\xc4\x81ntim \xc4\x81pnoti  \nnai\xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\xadhik\xc4\xabm  \nayukta\xe1\xb8\xa5 k\xc4\x81mak\xc4\x81re\xe1\xb9\x87a phale sakto nibadhyate 5.12  \n  \nsarvakarm\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87i manas\xc4\x81 sa\xe1\xb9\x83nyasy\xc4\x81ste sukha\xe1\xb9\x83 va\xc5\x9b\xc4\xab  \nnavadv\xc4\x81re pure deh\xc4\xab naiva kurvan na k\xc4\x81rayan 5.13  \n  \nna kart\xe1\xb9\x9btva\xe1\xb9\x83 na karm\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87i lokasya s\xe1\xb9\x9bjati prabhu\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nna karmaphalasa\xe1\xb9\x83yoga\xe1\xb9\x83 svabh\xc4\x81vas tu pravartate 5.14  \n  \nn\xc4\x81datte kasyacit p\xc4\x81pa\xe1\xb9\x83 na caiva suk\xe1\xb9\x9bta\xe1\xb9\x83 vibhu\xe1\xb8\xa5  \naj\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81nen\xc4\x81v\xe1\xb9\x9bta\xe1\xb9\x83 j\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81na\xe1\xb9\x83 tena muhyanti jantava\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.15  \n  \nj\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81nena tu tad aj\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81na\xe1\xb9\x83 ye\xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 n\xc4\x81\xc5\x9bitam \xc4\x81tmana\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nte\xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\x81m \xc4\x81dityavaj j\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81na\xe1\xb9\x83 prak\xc4\x81\xc5\x9bayati tat param 5.16  \n  \ntadbuddhayas tad\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81nas tanni\xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\xadh\xc4\x81s tatpar\xc4\x81ya\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5  \ngacchanty apunar\xc4\x81v\xe1\xb9\x9btti\xe1\xb9\x83 j\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81nanirdh\xc5\xabtakalma\xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.17  \n  \nvidy\xc4\x81vinayasa\xe1\xb9\x83panne br\xc4\x81hma\xe1\xb9\x87e gavi hastini  \n\xc5\x9buni caiva \xc5\x9bvap\xc4\x81ke ca pa\xe1\xb9\x87\xe1\xb8\x8dit\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5 samadar\xc5\x9bina\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.18  \n  \nihaiva tair jita\xe1\xb8\xa5 sargo ye\xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 s\xc4\x81mye sthita\xe1\xb9\x83 mana\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nnirdo\xe1\xb9\xa3a\xe1\xb9\x83 hi sama\xe1\xb9\x83 brahma tasm\xc4\x81d brahma\xe1\xb9\x87i te  \nsthit\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.19  \n  \nna prah\xe1\xb9\x9b\xe1\xb9\xa3yet priya\xe1\xb9\x83 pr\xc4\x81pya nodvijet pr\xc4\x81pya c\xc4\x81priyam  \nsthirabuddhir asa\xe1\xb9\x83m\xc5\xab\xe1\xb8\x8dho brahmavid brahma\xe1\xb9\x87i  \nsthita\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.20  \n  \nb\xc4\x81hyaspar\xc5\x9be\xe1\xb9\xa3v asakt\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81 vindaty \xc4\x81tmani yat sukham  \nsa brahmayogayukt\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81 sukham ak\xe1\xb9\xa3ayam a\xc5\x9bnute 5.21  \n  \nye hi sa\xe1\xb9\x83spar\xc5\x9baj\xc4\x81 bhog\xc4\x81 du\xe1\xb8\xa5khayonaya eva te  \n\xc4\x81dyantavanta\xe1\xb8\xa5 kaunteya na te\xe1\xb9\xa3u ramate budha\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.22  \n  \n\xc5\x9baknot\xc4\xabhaiva ya\xe1\xb8\xa5 so\xe1\xb8\x8dhu\xe1\xb9\x83 pr\xc4\x81k \xc5\x9bar\xc4\xabravimok\xe1\xb9\xa3a\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81t  \nk\xc4\x81makrodhodbhava\xe1\xb9\x83 vega\xe1\xb9\x83 sa yukta\xe1\xb8\xa5 sa sukh\xc4\xab nara\xe1\xb8\xa5  \n5.23  \n  \nyonta\xe1\xb8\xa5sukhontar\xc4\x81r\xc4\x81mas tath\xc4\x81ntarjyotir eva ya\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nsa yog\xc4\xab brahmanirv\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87a\xe1\xb9\x83 brahmabh\xc5\xabtodhigacchati 5.24  \n  \nlabhante brahmanirv\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87am \xe1\xb9\x9b\xe1\xb9\xa3aya\xe1\xb8\xa5 k\xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\xab\xe1\xb9\x87akalma\xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nchinnadvaidh\xc4\x81 yat\xc4\x81tm\xc4\x81na\xe1\xb8\xa5 sarvabh\xc5\xabtahite rat\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.25  \n  \nk\xc4\x81makrodhaviyukt\xc4\x81n\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 yat\xc4\xabn\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 yatacetas\xc4\x81m  \nabhito brahmanirv\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87a\xe1\xb9\x83 vartate vidit\xc4\x81tman\xc4\x81m 5.26  \n  \nspar\xc5\x9b\xc4\x81n k\xe1\xb9\x9btv\xc4\x81 bahir b\xc4\x81hy\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83\xc5\x9b cak\xe1\xb9\xa3u\xc5\x9b caiv\xc4\x81ntare  \nbhruvo\xe1\xb8\xa5  \npr\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81p\xc4\x81nau samau k\xe1\xb9\x9btv\xc4\x81 n\xc4\x81s\xc4\x81bhyantarac\xc4\x81ri\xe1\xb9\x87au 5.27  \n  \nyatendriyamanobuddhirmunir mok\xe1\xb9\xa3apar\xc4\x81ya\xe1\xb9\x87a\xe1\xb8\xa5  \nvigatecch\xc4\x81bhayakrodho ya\xe1\xb8\xa5 sad\xc4\x81 mukta eva sa\xe1\xb8\xa5 5.28  \n  \nbhokt\xc4\x81ra\xe1\xb9\x83 yaj\xc3\xb1atapas\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 sarvalokamahe\xc5\x9bvaram  \nsuh\xe1\xb9\x9bda\xe1\xb9\x83 sarvabh\xc5\xabt\xc4\x81n\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 j\xc3\xb1\xc4\x81tv\xc4\x81 m\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x83 \xc5\x9b\xc4\x81ntim \xe1\xb9\x9bcchati  \n5.29  \n  \n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI. atha \xe1\xb9\xa3a\xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\xadhodhy\xc4\x81ya\xe1\xb8\xa5. (\xc4\x81tmasa\xe1\xb9\x83yamayoga\xe1\xb8\xa5)](bgs06.htm)\n\n'